 and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas De Coudray was born about 1300 as the son of Thomas De Coudray and Juliana. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Lucy. He died on 16 May 1349, in Barton Stacey, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 50."},"et":{"about 1300–16 May 1349":"umbes 1300–16. mai 1349","1300–1349":"1300–1349","1305–1349":"1305–1349","–Female":"Surnud","1314–Male":"1314–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","–1348":"–1348","16 May 1349":"16. mai 1349","1305":"1305","1349":"1349","1348":"1348","1314":"1314","1300":"1300","about 1314":"umbes 1314","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1330":"1330","about 1300":"umbes 1300","about 1330":"umbes 1330","Barton Stacey, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Barton Stacey, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1300–16 May 1349":"noin 1300–16. toukokuuta 1349","1300–1349":"1300–1349","1305–1349":"1305–1349","–Female":"Kuollut","1314–Male":"1314–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","–1348":"–1348","16 May 1349":"16. toukokuuta 1349","1305":"1305","1349":"1349","1348":"1348","1314":"1314","1300":"1300","about 1314":"noin 1314","about 1348":"noin 1348","1330":"1330","about 1300":"noin 1300","about 1330":"noin 1330","Barton Stacey, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Barton Stacey, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1300–16 May 1349":"environ 1300–16 mai 1349","1300–1349":"1300–1349","1305–1349":"1305–1349","–Female":"Décédée","1314–Male":"1314–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","–1348":"–1348","16 May 1349":"1